Rules and basic principles

Any live cell with fewer than two live neighbors dies 
Any live cell with two or three live neighbors lives on to the next generation.
Any live cell with more than three live neighbors dies
Any dead cell with exactly three live neighbors becomes a live cell

The only input by the user is the initial state of the game (i.e. starting matrix), the game then plays itself until it reaches a steady state or is terminated. Thus the starting matrix and its layout is crucial for the way the game is played.
